<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="371" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,510,753]" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chretien" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[201,354,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Idaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobaria">
<emphasis box="[201,354,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Idaea lobaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group includes two species: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chretien" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[768,873,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Idaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobaria">
<emphasis box="[768,873,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">I. lobaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Guerrero &amp; Hausmann &amp; Ortiz, 2021" authorityName="Guerrero &amp; Hausmann &amp; Ortiz" authorityYear="2021" box="[927,1071,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Idaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="josephinae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[927,1071,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">I. josephinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1078,1165,511,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Male genitalia are characterized by the short, triangular uncus with narrowly truncate apex, shortly projecting saccus and shortly spatulate valva without spinules at the tip (
<figureCitation box="[544,677,582,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1923,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,1066,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-408@4.[161,1426,1066,1899]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Idaea lobaria (Chrétien, 1909).A. Male: Morocco, HighAtlas, Tiseldei, 1600 m, south of Tizi-n-Tichka, 29.05.2017, leg. and gen. prep. Rolf Bläsius; B. Male: Morocco, Anti-Atlas, 30 km northeast of Igherm, 1500 m, 30.05.2010, leg. Rolf Bläsius; C and D. Male genitalia and detailed aedeagus from specimen A. (Pictures courtesy of Harald Lahm in Lepiforum.de)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5025954" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5025954/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Figs 2A, B</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[693,768,582,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1142,1166]" captionTargetBox="[185,1400,221,1114]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[175,1413,199,1119]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Idaea josephinae sp. n. A. Male genitalia; B. Aedeagus; C. Female genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5025956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5025956/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">3C, D</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia present posterior apophyses measuring twice the length of the anterior apophyses, short ductus bursae, and a pyriform corpus bursae that is longitudinally furrowed in its posterior part. DNA barcodes cluster in three different BINs from the Iberian Peninsula (BOLD: ACD0706), across North Africa (BOLD:AEE5597) to 
<collectingCountry box="[771,833,690,716]" name="Israel" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Israel</collectingCountry>
(BOLD:ABZ0361). The further study of that genetic pattern was suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Muller, B. &amp; Erlacher, S. &amp; Hausmann, A. &amp; Rajaei, H. &amp; Sihvonen, P. &amp; Skou, P." box="[439,660,726,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" refId="ref4771" refString="Muller, B., Erlacher, S., Hausmann, A., Rajaei, H., Sihvonen, P. &amp; Skou, P. (2019) The Geometrid moths of Europe. Vol. 6. Part 1. Ennominae II. Brill, Leiden, 906 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004387485" type="book" year="2019">
Müller 
<emphasis box="[522,578,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hausmann, A. &amp; Muller, G. C. &amp; Kravchenko, V. D." box="[714,982,726,753]" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" refId="ref4535" refString="Hausmann, A., Muller, G. C. &amp; Kravchenko, V. D. (2020) The Lepidoptera of Israel. Vol. 3. Geometridae. Akademischer Verlag Munchen, Munich, 256 pp." type="book" year="2020">
Hausmann 
<emphasis box="[841,897,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
